---

ğŸ”¥ 1. What is Databricks?
- Cloud-based platform on Apache Spark
- Supports Python, SQL, Scala, R
- Integrates with AWS, Azure, GCP

---

âš¡ 2. Delta Lake â€“ The Smarter Data Lake
- ACID Transactions, Time Travel, Schema Evolution
- Faster queries with indexing & caching

Example SQL:
CREATE TABLE events (event_id STRING, event_type STRING) USING DELTA;

SELECT * FROM events VERSION AS OF 5;

---

ğŸ› ï¸ 3. Querying Data
SQL Example:
SELECT name, age FROM customers WHERE age > 25;

PySpark Example:
df = spark.read.format("delta").load("/mnt/data/customers")
df.filter(df.age > 25).show()

[IMAGE: pyspark-sql-operations.png]

---

ğŸ—ï¸ 4. Data Warehouse vs Data Lake vs Data Lakehouse
| Feature      | Warehouse | Data Lake | Lakehouse |
|-------------|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| Definition  | Structured storage | Raw data | Hybrid |
| Data Type   | Structured | Any | Structured + Semi |
| Performance | Fast | Slow | Balanced |
| Examples    | Snowflake | S3 | Databricks |

[IMAGE: dw-lake-lakehouse.png]

